# Session Memory — Implementation Plan

Build **Layer 13 — Controlled Session Memory** per §2.13. Provides Redis-backed state for conversational RAG interactions with strict limits on stored data to maintain quality and prevent hallucination compounding.

## Proposed Changes

### Schemas

#### [NEW] [schemas.py](file:///c:/HelioX/memory/schemas.py)

| Model | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `MemoryInteraction` | Replaces raw traces with: `query_id`, `original_query`, [sqo](file:///c:/HelioX/tests/test_workers.py#48-63) (intent/constraints only), and the `final_answer`. |
| `UserPreferences` | `format` (e.g., concise, detailed), `include_evidence`. |
| `SessionRecord` | Contains `session_id`, list of `History` objects (`MemoryInteraction`), and `UserPreferences`. |

### Engine & Storage

#### [NEW] [session_store.py](file:///c:/HelioX/memory/session_store.py)

- `RedisSessionStore(redis_url)`:
  - `get_session(session_id) -> SessionRecord`
  - `add_interaction(session_id, sqo, answer)`: Creates or updates the record. Explicitly guarantees we drop `worker_outputs`, `conflict_candidates`, and `reasoning_traces`.
  - Uses `redis.asyncio`.

#### [NEW] [lifecycle.py](file:///c:/HelioX/memory/lifecycle.py)

- `SessionLifecycleManager`:
  - `refresh_ttl(session_id)`: Bumps TTL to `30 minutes` (1800s) on every access.
  - `close_session(session_id)`: Optional manual expiration.

